					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This is a fragment of an inscription which should have recorded an exchange of some land belonging to a certain Rāyanarāyaṇaṉ probably with the one of the temple (of Vaikuṉṟattu-Niṉṟaruḷiya-Perumāḷ) at <hi rend="bold">Mahēndramaṅgalam.</hi> On the top of this stone is the concluding portion of another inscription which records a gift of land as a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna</hi> to the temple by a private individual.</p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
